          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Hello, folks. It's been a while since I did one of these. Like everyone else, I've been knocked for a loop by the rapid progress of Covid-19. Luckily, so far my family remains untouched by the novel coronavirus — but two local people I know are in hospital, and another is recovering. ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "The last three weeks have been frantic. I've been trying to reconfigure my face-to-face training courses to online format - which seems (so far) to be working - while seeking alternative revenue streams. And I'm doing that while home schooling my daughters for half a day every weekday. ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "type": "image",
        "src": "__GHOST_URL__/content/images/2020/04/IMG_3108.jpeg",
        "alt": "Home schooling during Covid-19 lockdown",
        "cardWidth": "wide"
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "It's ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 2,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "exhausting",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": ".",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "But this is our new normal, for now at least, so on we go. Here's some things I think you should be taking note of right now.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalrule"
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Tracking the coronavirus through social media data",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "heading",
        "tag": "h2",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "I always emphasise to the Interhacktives that one way you can view social media is as a vast data set they can interrogate through their data journalism skills. This takes that idea about 15 steps further:",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "type": "bookmark",
        "url": "https://www.scientificamerican.com/article/social-media-posts-and-online-searches-hold-vital-clues-about-pandemic-spread/",
        "metadata": {
          "url": "https://www.scientificamerican.com/article/social-media-posts-and-online-searches-hold-vital-clues-about-pandemic-spread/",
          "title": "Social Media Posts and Online Searches Hold Vital Clues about Pandemic Spread",
          "description": "Such data offer valuable information and could help track the novel coronavirus&mdash;but they risk errors and raise privacy concerns",
          "author": "Katherine Ellison,Knowable Magazine",
          "publisher": "Scientific American",
          "thumbnail": "https://static.scientificamerican.com/sciam/cache/file/1DF69F98-D74A-4237-8D7C2B4791A330F5.jpg",
          "icon": "https://www.scientificamerican.com/public/resources/favicons/favicon-196-f10395ba7ecf07756e4b5a82c4795b61.png"
        }
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Exciting stuff. ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "The platforms tentatively step up",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "heading",
        "tag": "h2",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "While my own financial situation is much more perilous than it was only a few weeks ago, many have it much worse. Facebook is doing something to support local media survive what could be an ad-collapse apocalypse. ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "However, as I've been helping local voluntary organisations with their web and social media presence, I can't help wondering if they could have ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 2,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "more",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": " impact by finding ways of getting decent reach on locally-important posts without charging people for them right now. ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "type": "bookmark",
        "url": "https://www.nytimes.com/2020/03/30/business/facebook-media-coronavirus.html",
        "metadata": {
          "url": "https://www.nytimes.com/2020/03/30/business/facebook-media-coronavirus.html",
          "title": "Facebook Aims $100 Million at Media Hit by the Coronavirus",
          "description": "With grants and marketing spending, the social media giant hopes to support outlets doing essential local reporting but struggling with a drop in advertising.",
          "author": "Marc Tracy",
          "publisher": "NYTimes",
          "thumbnail": "https://static01.nyt.com/images/2020/03/30/business/30facebooknews1/30facebooknews1-facebookJumbo.jpg",
          "icon": "https://www.nytimes.com/vi-assets/static-assets/apple-touch-icon-319373aaf4524d94d38aa599c56b8655.png"
        }
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Meanwhile, Twitter is finally starting to delete Tweets from major political figures that contain gross untruths:",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
